THE Maluti Regional Court sentenced a 29-year-old man to life in jail for killing his girlfriend. On 23 October 2020, Khitleli Boitumelo attacked his girlfriend, Makumane Mpherwane (26), and another woman. The women were travelling in Mpherwane’s vehicle. ALSO READ: Boy (14) shoots girlfriend 3 times! Boitumelo pelted the vehicle with stones, forcing Mpherwane to stop. Boitumelo then stabbed them. Mpherwane died and the other woman survived. He was sentenced to life in prison for murder and received a 10-year sentence for attempted murder. Eastern Cape police boss Lieutenant-General Nomthetheleli Mene welcomed the sentences.